1) Get the required software

The system runs on the 12.04.2 LTS Ubuntu Linux 64-bit distribution.  You should install
this distro before proceeeding.
The ISO file is available at: http://old-releases.ubuntu.com/releases/12.04.2/ubuntu-12.04.4-server-amd64.iso.

2) Build and install

2.0) One-time setup

$ cd <omniplay>/scripts
$ ./setup.sh
$ source $HOME/.omniplay_setup

2.1) Build the Omniplay kernel 

$ cd $OMNIPLAY_DIR/linux-lts-quantal-3.5.0
$ mv theia64.config .config
$ ./compile
$ sudo make modules_install
$ ./compile
$ sudo reboot

2.2) Build glibc
install textinfo:
$ cd dependencies.yang/textinfo;
$ sudo apt-get install libncurses5-dev
$ sudo apt-get install gawk autoconf gettext
$ sudo apt-get install help2man
$ ./configure; make; sudo make install

$ cd $OMNIPLAY_DIR/eglibc-2.15/
$ mkdir build
$ mkdir prefix
$ cd build
$ ../configure --prefix=$OMNIPLAY_DIR/eglibc-2.15/prefix --disable-profile --enable-add-on --without-gd --without-selinux --without-cvs --enable-kernel=3.2.0 --target=x86_64-linux-gnu --host=x86_64-linux-gnu
$ make
$ mkdir /var/db
$ chown <user> /var/db
$ touch ../prefix/etc/ld.so.conf
$ make install
$ cd $OMNIPLAY_DIR/eglibc-2.15/prefix
$ ln -s /usr/lib/locale

2.3) Build the tool
$ cd $OMNIPLAY_DIR/test/dev
$ make
$ cd ..
$ make

